The Chief Executive Officer, Glittering Health Beauty and Brow, Aremu Yayah, has tasked youths to rebrand themselves through entrepreneurial skills.
 
Speaking in Lagos recently, Yayah, said the outfit has improved most youths’ mind-sets, who have added value to the society.
   
He said: “We organise entrepreneurship skills workshop to groom, package and fortify them to meet up with modern challenge. “I have trained over 2000 persons to do their businesses over the years; we have employed a lot of youths in our Ikeja, Lekki, Abuja and Ghana branches.”  She pointed out that some qualities that make a personal brand stand out, such as – referrals, appearance, behavior communication and platform. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .